window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From </b><b><i>New York Times</i></b><b> best-selling author Joanne DeMaio comes a riveting love story set in a quaint New England town. </b></p> <p>An old farmhouse, winding country lanes, red barns and wishing fountains...all are the backdrop to Amy Trewist's simple days in Addison, Connecticut. Until she's in the wrong place at the wrong time. </p> <p>Just like George Carbone. When he crosses paths with Amy that fateful morning, their two summers blend. As George and Amy come to lean on each other, their broken hearts begin to heal. But an unexpected twist in this secret-filled small town could change everything.</p>"; 
